  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed development, by reason of its layout, self-contained facilities, and independent access via a gated side passage, represents a form of backland residential intensification that fails to respect the established urban grain and street pattern. The introduction of a separate dwelling to the rear of the host property results in a cramped and uncharacteristic form of development that does not relate well to the surrounding context and would be detrimental to the character of the surrounding area. \r\rThe proposal is therefore contrary to Policies D3, D4 and D6 of the London Plan (2021), to policy 30 of the Enfield Core Strategy (2010), to policies DMD6, DMD7, DMD8, DMD12 and DMD37 of the Enfield Development Management Document (2014), and to Section 12 of the NPPF (2024)\r",
    "The proposed development would result in a substandard quality of accommodation that fails to provide a high-quality living environment for future occupants. The internal layout lacks any meaningful separation between living, sleeping, and kitchen areas, resulting in a cramped and poorly functioning space. The single-aspect design, combined with a limited outlook constrained by a 1.8-metre-high boundary fence located just 3 metres from the primary window, creates an enclosed and oppressive living environment with poor levels of outlook and visual amenity. \r\rThe proposal therefore fails to provide a satisfactory standard of accommodation contrary to Policy D6 of the London Plan (2021), to policy CP30 of the Enfield Core Strategy (2010), to policies DMD8 and DMD37 of the Enfield Development Management Document (2014), and to Section 12 of the NPPF (2024)\r"
  ],
